main event: On April 20, 1963, a civilian observed a bright object in the sky for approximately 1-5 minutes, which was later concluded to be Jupiter.
interesting points: The object appeared star-like and luminous,The observer noted that Jupiter was at an angular elevation of around 65 degrees at one point during the observation,The sighting took place in Cincinnati, Ohio,The object faded out of view after a few minutes,The observer experienced partial obscuration by clouds during the sighting.
sighted object: a bright object resembling a star
witness description: The witness described the object as a flat disc-shaped glowing object, approximately 20-30 feet in diameter, that moved silently across the sky.
